    "description": "Becton Dickinson India Global Group is actively seeking a talented and motivated Radiologist to join our dynamic team in Vijayawada. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Becton Dickinson India Global Group:\nBecton Dickinson India Global Group is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Post Graduate Diploma in relevant field\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Referral bonus program\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Learning & development budget\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Becton Dickinson India Global Group!",
